                        <interp inst="t18400302-name-1041" type="given" value="JESSE"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18400302-987-offence-1 t18400302-name-1041"></join>Jesse Hill</persName>.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18400302-name-1042" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18400302-name-1042" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400302-name-1042" type="surname" value="HILL"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400302-name-1042" type="given" value="JESSE"></interp>JESSE HILL</persName>
                  </hi>. I keep a public-house in Hughes's-fields, Deptford. The prisoner had frequented my house about six months—on the 7th of Febru<lb></lb>ary, he came about seven o'clock, and called for a pint of half-and-half—I went into the room where he was sitting about ten o'clock, and I saw his hat placed in a dark corner, and the tumbler now produced was behind it—in consequence of that I spoke to the policeman—the prisoner went away about ten minutes past eleven o'clock—I then went into the parlour, and missed the tumbler—I came back, and saw him in custody—the po<lb></lb>liceman showed me this tumbler—this other glass and this spoon were found on him at the station-house—they are all mine.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner. Q.</hi> Did you ever know a dishonest action of me before? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> No.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18400302-name-1043" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18400302-name-1043" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400302-name-1043" type="surname" value="CHURCHEE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400302-name-1043" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>HENRY CHURCHEE</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable R</hi> 109.) I took the prisoner when he got about one hundred yards from the prosecutor's house—I found this tumbler in his hat—I found this spoon and this small glass in his trowsers pocket at the station-house.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> I had been drinking all the evening, and when I came away I was rather the worse for liquor—I was not aware that I had it.</p>
